<br>
I'm new to this board.  I have a level 42 Mage who has yet to get any pet summoning focus items.  I've perused the board and read a few things like mermaid scales... but the info is scetchy that I've found.<br>
<br>
Is there somewhere on this board that has a complete list of items, areas and what you do with them to get the shovel, etc for summoning pets?  If so, I'd really appreciate being pointed in that direction.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance,<br>
Pariza Phireheart, 42 Mage, Notabilis Kruoris, Inny Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaladini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#333333>(6/18/02 6:23:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is the specific info on Pet Focus items?</span><hr size=1> Actually, the best source would be www.magecompendium.com (or click on the Gnogaine add above.) Then click on the link called Focus items.<br>
<br>
The focus items are pretty straight forward to get (not sure if you're looking for the low or high level items). For the low level ones, most of your time will be spent camping greens in Najena, with a few annoying trips across norrath for miscellaneous components.<br>
<br>
Naladini <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaladini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naladini</A> at: 6/18/02 6:26:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uodibillauxes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odibil Lauxes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 12:09:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is the specific info on Pet Focus items?</span><hr size=1> The Solusek Ro focus item quests become obsolete after your 49 series of pets. Vocarations (51-54), Dyzil's Deafening Decoy (56), and Greater Vocarations (57-60) will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be affected by these focus items, only Staves of Elemental Mastery.<br>
<br>
Being that you're only 7 levels away from being trivial, I would start by obtaining the items for Shovel of Ponz and Broom of Trilon, since you'll need them to complete your epic, if you ever decide to go that route.<br>
<br>
If by then, you think that you'll find use of the other focus items, then by all means, complete the Torch of Alna and Stein of Ulissa quests. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1515<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 12:26:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is the specific info on Pet Focus items?</span><hr size=1> I found the 49 Fire pet occasionally useful, and until I got my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velious Mage Bracer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the torch was the item I carried around for reclaim energy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utharngor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tharngor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 1:19:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is the specific info on Pet Focus items?</span><hr size=1> This is what i would recommend for doing this quests.<br>
<br>
1. Start in OOT, go to mermaid islands near the zone to BB and kill the mermaids to get mermaid scales.<br>
2. Go to spec island kill skels to get gargoyles to spawn, kill gargs get gargoyle eyes.<br>
3. Ask the person who is camping gornit/dornit if you can have the giant toes drops, fire, ice, hill. Check the erollisi vendor for cyclops toes usually has them, or ask the person camping dornit/gornit and see if they have them. <br>
(Gornit/Dornit is perm camped due to the large amounts of cash dropped)<br>
4. Go to freeport all the gems can be bought from vendors for around 80 - 150pp average each no big deal. just look in www.eqtraders.com jewlery section for a list of gem vendors and what they sell. <br>
<br>
Can remember the full list of exact gems needed atm. but i think it ruby, Saphire, star saphire, emerald or something like that.<br>
<br>
5. Go to EC/WC check all the vendors for Griffon feather(s), usually there are some on a vendor, if not pop to EK and kill a few griffs.<br>
6. Go to Lavastorm and kill the drakes to get fire drake scale.<br>
7. Then go to najena, and kill the female dark elf magicians (there are lots just cycle them, can do named, goblin as they can also drop components required) to get Broom, Shovel, torch, stien.<br>
8. Then go to Temple and do the hand-ins.<br>
<br>
I got all 4 focus items at Level 29 Solo in about 6 hours. <p><table><tr><td>
<b>Thangor ElementalFriend</b><br>
Mage of Povar</td></tr>
